cd /usr/ports/news/suck; make install

CPFong@News-> which suck
/usr/local/bin/suck

CPFong@News-> pwd
/usr/ports/news/suck/work/suck-4.3.0/sample
cp get.news.inn ~news/bin/

Try to use suck now. Step by Step:
CPFong@News-> which suck
/usr/local/bin/suck
CPFong@News-> pwd
/home/cpfong
CPFong@News-> whoami
cpfong

CPFong@News-> suck
Attempting to connect to localhost
Using Port 119
Official host name: localhost.fjtc.edu.tw
Alias localhost
Address: 127.0.0.1
Connected to localhost.fjtc.edu.tw
200 news.FJTC.edu.tw InterNetNews server INN 2.3.3 ready
/usr/home/cpfong/sucknewsrc: No such file or directory
Elapsed Time = 0 mins 0.00 seconds
Closed connection to localhost

CPFong@News-> cat sucknewsrc 
#group  artile start number
test    1

CPFong@News-> suck -M
..... OK now
note: one suck.newrc is generated by system automatically

CPFong@News-> suck -M -c
clean up myself (check the man suck)

CPFong@News-> mkdir .suck
CPFong@News-> vi .suck/sucknewsrc
#group  artile start number
test    1

CPFong@News-> suck -M -dd ~/.suck -dt ~/.suck
CFong@News-> ls .suck/
suck.newrc      sucknewsrc

CPFong@News-> suck -M -c -dd ~/.suck -dt ~/.suck
CPFong@News-> suck -M -c -dd ~/.suck -dt ~/.suck -hl localhost
CPFong@News-> suck -M -dd ~/.suck -dt ~/.suck -hl localhost -dm ~/tmp
CPFong@News-> suck -M -dd ~/.suck -dt ~/.suck -hl localhost -dm ~/tmp/articles -m
CPFong@News-> ls tmp/articles/
01-10   02-10   03-10   04-10   05-10   06-10   07-10   08-10   09-10   10-10
CPFong@News-> suck -M -dd ~/.suck -dt ~/.suck -hl localhost -dm ~/tmp/articles -m -bi bfile
PFong@News-> cat bfile 
/home/cpfong/tmp/articles/01-10
/home/cpfong/tmp/articles/02-10
